summary:
I am a huge challenge lover,  fond of solving problems and puzzles, especially those others cannot solve. Always want to be an expert in quantitative finance field. Working with smart people is a pleasure for me, I like the atmosphere that everyone in the team has something to offer.spent my first two decades in math then I found applying math in finance is more awesome. So I chose to pursue master degree of  Financial Engineering  in NYU Tandon. In academic field, thinking myself as a skill connecting tree and always trying to add more and new nodes on that. Here is how the tree grows till now: Programming:  C++, Python, SQL, Octave, Matlab, Excel VBA, Bloomberg Terminal, Microsoft OfficeDerivatives Pricing: Black-Scholes, Vasicek, CIR, Hull White, Heston, Feynman-Kac, Girsanov, Q measure, T measureMath: VaR, ARIMA, EWMA, ARCH, GARCH, Logistic Regression, Variance Reduction, MLE, Monte Carlo, TSA, Finite difference method, ADF testTrading Strategies: Mean Reversion Trading, Trending Trading, Market Neutral, Statistical Arbitrage, Kalman filter                              When I am not working,  I like solving some puzzles on Hackerrank.com or publish something on github.com.   I like sharing my experience and thoughts with people and listening to their ideas on weekends. Besides, work-out is  a must for me, 5 times a week on weekdays. If you want to know more about me, or  have an  cash printer idea but don't know how to build it, feel free to contact me through:  cy946@nyu.edu  ,I am here.

summary:
I am a licensed lawyer in US, Brazil and Portugal with several years of experience, and I am currently working on as Compliance Analyst at J.P. Morgan in New York City. Prior to J.P. Morgan, I worked as an Associate at a large scale securities litigation class action case for Pomerantz LLP. Before to moving to the US, I was working as Paralegal for a British law firm in the field of European Law and Immigration. Before that, I took an LL.M at BPP University in London, and an International Business Law post graduate course at King's College. I was a lawyer in a Brazilian firm, where I was working in the fields of administrative law, including public-private partnerships tenders, and arbitrage. I have well-honed skills in organizational and time management, drafting and negotiating a broad range of legal documents, working with arbitration, performing due diligence, and managing complex civil and commercial litigation matters.  I am fluent in English, Portuguese and Spanish, and have worked and been educated in both the Common Law system (LL.M in the United Kingdom) and the Civil Law system (Brazilian Law degree). I am currently undertaking a part time Certificate in Business Finance Fundamentals at NYU.I am a member of the Brazilian Bar, Portuguese Bar and Illinois Bar.***To contact me please email nataliacamposrocha@gmail.com.

summary:
Victoria Poulakis recently graduated from Fordham University’s Gabelli School of Business where she earned her Bachelors of Science in Business Administration with a concentration in Finance, and a minor in Business Law and Ethics. She currently works at J.P. Morgan Chase as an analyst on the Fixed Income Regulation Team. Through her undergraduate studies at Fordham, she has developed a strong aspiration for a career in the financial services industry. She is prepared to apply her strong work ethic and interpersonal skills to continue to learn and gain valuable experience within the field.

summary:
Vincent Russo is an Investment Bank Credit Analyst at JP Morgan. At JPM, he is in the Financial Institutions Group, more specifically, Banks and Broker Dealers. Vincent's clients include bulge bracket banks, regional banks, community banks, credit card processors, central counterparty clearing houses and exchanges.Vincent graduated from Fordham University's Gabelli School of Business with a major in Finance and a concentration in Value Investing. Previously, Vincent was a Summer Analyst at JP Morgan performing the same role. Prior to this, he interned in the Asset Management Department of UBS for 2 years. Vincent graduated Timber Creek Regional High School in 2013 where he earned the honors of Valedictorian and Class President.
